Class QueuedTask

java.lang.Object
  com.google.code.sagetvaddons.sjq.shared.Task
      com.google.code.sagetvaddons.sjq.shared.QueuedTask
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
public class QueuedTask
extends Task

A QueuedTask is a Task which has been added to the queue; it contains additional deatils such as which client is running it, the state of the task, what time it was created, etc.

Constructor

Parameters:
qId - The unique task queue id assigned to this task
id - The task id for the task
requiredResources - The number of resources required to perform this task on the assigned task client
maxInstances - The max number of instances of this task that can run at once on the assigned task client
schedule - The task's active schedule; crontab format
executable - The executable path for this task
exeArguments - The command line arguments for the exe
maxTime - The maximum amount of time this task can run before being killed; ignored for SJQ script exes
maxTimeRatio - Not implemented
minReturnCode - The minimum return code considered a success
maxReturnCode - The maximum return code considered a success
metadata - The env vars to be injected into the runtime env for BOTH the exe and the test script
created - When this task was added to the queue
assigned - The date this task was last assigned to a task client
completed - The date this task was last completed/returned by a task client
state - The current state of the task
assignee - The last Client assigned this task or null if the task is currently assigned to no one
serverHost - The hostname of the SJQ server that assigned this task
serverPort - The port of the SJQ server agent that assigned this task
test - The name of a pretest script to execute for this task or null if no test is to be ran
testArgs - Optional args to be provided to the test script; currently not implemented
rmiPort - The sagex-api RMI port for the Sage server hosting the SJQ server that assigned this task

Parameters:
t - The base Task instance this QueuedTask is based on
qId - The unique task queue id assigned to this task
metadata - The env var map for the task
created - The date this task was added to the queue
assigned - The date it was last assigned to a client
completed - The date it was last returned by a client
state - The state of the task
assignee - The last client assigned this task or null if never assigned to a client
serverHost - The SJQ server that assigned this task
serverPort - The port that the SJQ server agent is listening on
rmiPort - The sagex-api RMI port for the Sage server host running the SJQ server that assigned this task
